# Cloudflare Pages redirects.
#
# Real files in the output root (every prerendered route folder like /about,
# /activities/atv-buggy-tours, plus /robots.txt, /sitemap.xml, /llms.txt) are
# served directly before any rule below fires. These rules only apply to URLs
# that don't match a real file.
#
# Admin routes stay SPA-routed so the client-side auth flow can hand off.
/admin       /index.html   200
/admin/*     /index.html   200

# Everything else → the prerendered 404 page with a real 404 status. Prevents a
# soft-404 (200 + the SPA shell) on unknown URLs.
/*           /404.html     404
